p: The developed MCC location tree file was then feed to SPREAD (version 1.0.7) software to visualize the phylogeographic output of the MCC tree and the discrete tree phylogenetic module was utilized to generate the.xml file and the location coordinates were fed separately. The results of the phylogeographic analysis confirmed the migration of the DENV-2 Cosmopolitan Clade 1b viruses to Sri Lanka from the South-East Asian region ( Fig 8).
